### Review Checklist

Work through each category systematically:

#### 1. Architecture & Design

- [ ] **Single Responsibility**: Each package/file/function does ONE thing well
- [ ] **Dependency Direction**: Dependencies flow inward (handlers â†’ services â†’ domain)
- [ ] **Interface Segregation**: Small, focused interfaces over large ones
- [ ] **No Circular Dependencies**: Clean dependency graph
- [ ] **Appropriate Abstraction Level**: Not over-engineered, not under-engineered

#### 2. Code Quality

- [ ] **DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)**: No copy-paste code; extract common patterns
- [ ] **Naming**: Clear, intention-revealing names (not `x`, `temp`, `data`)
- [ ] **Function Size**: Functions are small and focused (~30 lines max, exceptions for tables/switch)
- [ ] **Error Handling**: Errors are handled explicitly, not swallowed
